{"number":58434,"title":"[HDInsight] Docs: Update README with service-specific content, key concepts, and code examples","body":"## Documentation Gap

**Package:** `Azure.ResourceManager.HDInsight`
**Service directory:** `sdk/hdinsight/Azure.ResourceManager.HDInsight/`
**Triggered by:** commit 9939c2e97 (PR #57044) by `@live1206`

## What Changed

The package was migrated from AutoRest/Swagger to TypeSpec-based code generation (#57044). New `ModelFactory` methods were added for several types (`HDInsightClusterCreateOrUpdateContent`, `HDInsightClusterRole`, `HDInsightSecurityProfile`, etc.) and API version was upgraded to include Entra User support as cluster administrator credentials.

## Gaps Found

- **No service-specific Key Concepts section** — the current README links to generic SDK docs instead of describing HDInsight-specific resource types (e.g., `HDInsightClusterResource`, `HDInsightApplicationResource`, `HDInsightClusterCollection`)
- **No code examples** — the Examples section only points to a generic samples link; there are no inline code snippets showing how to create, list, update, or delete HDInsight clusters or applications
- **No test-backed snippets** — there is no `tests/Samples/` directory at all; the test directory only contains `Scenario/` tests
- **Missing Entra User / new API feature documentation** — the CHANGELOG describes Entra User as cluster administrator (added in 1.2.0-beta.5) but the README does not mention this capability
- **&#34;Getting started&#34; section is incomplete** — it lacks a concrete example of authenticating and creating a `HDInsightClusterResource` client


<strong>📐 Implementation Guide</strong>

This section contains step-by-step instructions for a coding agent to implement the changes described above.

### Step 1: Modify files

**Edit** `sdk/hdinsight/Azure.ResourceManager.HDInsight/README.md`:

Replace the generic boilerplate **Key concepts** section with HDInsight-specific content:

```markdown
## Key concepts

### HDInsightClusterResource

An `HDInsightClusterResource` represents a single HDInsight cluster. It exposes operations to get, update, delete, resize, rotate disk encryption keys, and retrieve monitoring/gateway settings.

### HDInsightClusterCollection

`HDInsightClusterCollection` is obtained from a resource group and provides operations to create, list, and check existence of HDInsight clusters.

### HDInsightApplicationResource

`HDInsightApplicationResource` represents an application installed on an HDInsight cluster. It exposes CRUD operations for cluster applications.

### Thread safety

We guarantee that all client instance methods are thread-safe and independent of each other ([guideline]((azure.github.io/redacted)

### Additional concepts
[Client options](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#configuring-service-clients-using-clientoptions) |
[Accessing the response](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#accessing-http-response-details-using-responset) |
[Long-running operations](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#consuming-long-running-operations-using-operationt) |
[Handling failures](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#reporting-errors-requestfailedexception) |
[Diagnostics](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#logging) |
[Mocking](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/blob/main/sdk/core/Azure.Core/README.md#mocking) |
[Client lifetime]((devblogs.microsoft.com/redacted)
```

